snippet.title: Suspect wanted in triple homicide, Amber Alert in St. Louis County fatally shoots himself
snippet.description:
ST. LOUIS COUNTY, Mo. - The man wanted in an early morning Amber Alert and triple homicide of a mother and her two children in St. Louis County has died after shooting himself, multiple police sources have confirmed with 5 On Your Side.

Sources told reporter Christine Byers that officers were trying to arrest Bobby McCulley III on Clinton Street in the Old North St. Louis neighborhood in north city when he shot himself while sitting inside a car.

The investigation first started at 11:32 p.m. Thursday when a call came in for a shooting in the 4800 block of Lockwig Trail, which is in north county near Florissant.

Officers found a 34-year-old woman, her 13-year-old son and 6-year-old daughter shot to death inside a house, St. Louis County police confirmed. Their names have not been released.

Read more: https://www.ksdk.com/article/news/crime/st-louis-county-triple-homicide-amber-alert/63-1422ab06-e052-41f2-81f6-5da4067e5b04
